    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "`USE_BUNDLED_BUSTED` was added in https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/2447 (https://github.com/neovim/neovim/commit/fe9ec9c29956cb2bd4062d3e582412006d42292e), with the intention to skip building of deps needed for tests.\r\n\r\nFrom the name itself I understand it however as it would affect only \"busted\" itself, and not test dependencies in general.\r\nI.e. that you could use `USE_BUNDLED_BUSTED=0`, and still have tests working, when `USE_BUNDLED_LUAROCKS=1` was used by default.\r\n\r\nI think the current behavior is OK, but at least the description should be clarified / extended then: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/b5aecfe254fbe518801e57b0224dddf863aa069c/third-party/cmake/BuildLuarocks.cmake#L6\r\n\r\nAlso renaming it to `USE_BUNDLED_TEST_ROCKS` would make it more explicit (but should keep the old name anyway I guess).",
